TITLE: Defining a Basic Vala Class with Fields, Constructor, and Method
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a class that inherits from GLib.Object with public and private fields, a constructor, and a method. The class showcases different access modifiers and basic object-oriented features in Vala.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vala-lang/vala-docs/blob/main/source/tutorials/programming-language/main/03-00-object-oriented-programming/03-01-basics.rst#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: vala
CODE:
```
public class TestClass : GLib.Object {

    /* Fields */
    public int first_data = 0;
    private int second_data;

    /* Constructor */
    public TestClass() {
        this.second_data = 5;
    }

    /* Method */
    public int method_1() {
        stdout.printf("private data: %d", this.second_data);
        return this.second_data;
    }
}
```

