TITLE: Implementing Abstract Classes in Vala
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create an abstract class with abstract methods in Vala. The Animal class contains both a concrete method (eat) and an abstract method (say_hello) that must be implemented by subclasses Tiger and Duck.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vala-lang/vala-docs/blob/main/source/tutorials/programming-language/main/03-00-object-oriented-programming/03-07-abstract-classes.rst#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: vala
CODE:
```
public abstract class Animal : Object {

    public void eat() {
        stdout.printf("*chomp chomp*\n");
    }

    public abstract void say_hello();
}

public class Tiger : Animal {

    public override void say_hello() {
        stdout.printf("*roar*\n");
    }
}

public class Duck : Animal {

    public override void say_hello() {
        stdout.printf("*quack*\n");
    }
}
```

