TITLE: Defining a Generic Class in Vala
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines a generic class `Wrapper` in Vala. The class is parameterized by a type `G`, which is used as the type of the `data` property. This allows instances of the `Wrapper` class to store data of a specific type determined at instantiation.
